The '''[[Master of Laws|Mr.]] Hans van Mierlo Foundation''' ({{lang-nl|Mr. Hans van Mierlo Stichting}}) is a [[Netherlands|Dutch]] [[Think tank|policy institute]] linked to the [[Democrats 66]] (D66) party. The foundation is named after journalist and politician [[Hans van Mierlo]] the co-founder of the [[Democrats 66]]. The institute was formed on 1972 as the ({{lang-nl|Stichting Wetenschappelijk Bureau}}) and was renamed as the ({{lang-nl|Kenniscentrum D66}}) in 2003. On 7 May 2011 the institute was renamed again in honor of co-founder [[Hans van Mierlo]] who had died on 11 March 2010.<ref>{{nl icon}} {{cite web|url=http://www.nu.nl/politiek/2203438/hans-van-mierlo-overleden.html|title=Hans van Mierlo overleden|publisher=NU.nl|accessdate=12 March 2010}}</ref><ref>{{nl icon}} {{cite web|url=http://www.volkskrant.nl/binnenland/kenniscentrum-d66-heet-nu-hans-van-mierlo-stichting~a2074912/|title=Kenniscentrum D66 heet nu 'Hans van Mierlo stichting'|publisher=Volkskrant|accessdate=7 May 2011}}</ref>
